sources.description:
Unspeakable Horrors From Outer Space Paralyze The Living And Resurrect The Dead!
A team of brave individuals unite to confront evil alien's intent on resurrecting the dead and preventing mankind from creating a destructive weapon. With flying saucers appearing in the sky, they must save humanity from the impending threat.

Original title: Plan 9 from Outer Space (1957)


Black & white version: https://youtu.be/qsb74pW7goU

Director & Writer: Edward D. Wood Jr.
Cast: Bela Lugosi, Tor Johnson, Mona McKinnon, Gregory Walcott, Tom Keene, Lyle Talbot
Genres: B-movie, Cult film, Horror, Sci-Fi
Budget: $60,000

00:00 Full length movie.
00:10 Uncovering a mysterious and shocking tale of grave robbers from outer space in a cult horror film.
11:29 Interstellar beings visit Earth, causing chaos and secrecy among military and civilians.
22:45 Government officials deny existence. Plan 9 involves resurrecting the dead using electrodes. Concerns over flying saucers and graveyard incidents.
29:27 A mysterious cemetery disturbance leads to a missing body and a saucer sighting, prompting further investigation.
43:53 Alien message warns Earth of destruction due to advanced technology and urges peaceful coexistence.
48:10 Aliens attempt to use Earth's dead to prove their existence and gain acceptance, leading to a series of mysterious events.
1:01:13 Alien soldiers seek Earth's aid after being misunderstood and mistaken for enemies in a sci-fi horror cult film.
1:05:27 Alien warns Earth of destructive power of solaronite bomb, urges to stop before destroying universe.
1:11:32 Alien invasion threat sparks chaos and disbelief among humans in a cult sci-fi horror film.
